Azure checklist
	1.	Create a tenant
	2.	Create a user
	3.	Create a group
	4.	Switch tenants – But why? (to switch from personal to co-pass/tenant)
	5.	Create a role
	6.	Create a custom role (available only on P2)
	7.	Create a custom domain in AAD
	8.	Create a dynamic group in AAD
	9.	Assign a license to a user
	10.	Add any role to users
	11.	Create an administrative unit
	12.	Browse devices settings in AAD
	13.	Try bulk operations like create 10 users with csv file
	14.	Create external user
	15.	Enable some users/groups to reset their own password
	16.	What is AAD connect?

RBAC
	17. Add roles to the user to access storage account specific container
  	18. Create a custom role to remove delete permission of blob data
  	19. Give full contributor role in resource group scope  

Manage subscriptions and Governance:
	20. Create a subscription
	21. Create a cost alert in subscription.
	22. Create a budget in subscription.
	23. Create a resource lock in resource group.
	24. Create a policy to only be able to create certain size of VMs
	25. Test policy
	26. Check policy compliance.
	27. Move resources from one resource group to other subscription/region.
	28. Create a management group

Storage account:
  	29. Create a storage account
  	30. Create a container
  	31. Create a file share
  	32. Create a Queue
  	33. Create a table
 	34. Generate a SAS (shared access signature) to access blob container content
  	35. Create a stored access policy for a container/object
	36. Enable geo-redundant storage.
  	37. Recover file share via soft delete enable.
  	38. Take a snapshot of a container
  	39. Enable versioning of a container content.
  	40.	Create an alert rule in storage account monitoring.
	41.	Use azcopy to copy content from one storage account to other.
	42.	Perform object replication in storage account.
	43.	Create an Azure File share.
	44.	Deploy Azure File sync.

Azure Virtual Machines:
	45. Create a virtual machine
	46. Create a bastion service
	47. Create a vm scale set

ARM Template
	48. Create an arm template spec.
	49. Use a bash script for VM creation.
	50. Use an existing disk for a new VM
	51. Encrypt the disk used by VM by SSE and ADE

Webapp
	52. Create a webapp
	53. Explore web app deployment options and deployment slots
	54. Create/explore backups.

Azure container instance
	55. Create an azure container instance.
	56. Create an container group

